@ifinfo
@sc{atoms} is a program for generating lists of atomic coordinates from
crystallographic data.  The primary use of @sc{atoms} is to create input
files suitable for running the @i{ab initio} XAFS program @sc{feff}.  For
that purpose, the list is sorted by radial distance from an atom chosen
as the central atom.  @sc{atoms} can also generate other sorts of lists as
well as calculate estimations of the bulk absorption and density of the
crystal and various corrections to EXAFS data due to experimental
effects.
@end ifinfo



