@node Naming Conventions , Obtaining, What is new since version 2.42 , Program Notes
@section Naming Conventions

Between versions 2.41 and 2.42, my program had a name change. Earlier
versions were called @sc{atom}, while later versions are called
@sc{atoms}, with an @sc{s}. The reason for this change was to avoid
confusion with the subroutine @code{atom} that is an important part of
@sc{feff}. Hopefully this reduces confusion rather than adds to it!
For now, the version number is incremented by 0.01 when minor
functionality is added and by 0.1 when major functionality is added.
Bug corrections have been denoted with an incrementing letter appended
to the version number.


