@node Pure Elements , Common Lattice Types , Examples, Examples
@section Pure Elements


These are examples of @code{atoms.inp} files for several pure
elements.

@table @r
@item The following elements commonly crystallize in the bcc structure:
Li, Na, K, V, Cr, Fe, Rb, Nb, Mo, Cs, Ba, Ta, W, Eu
@item The following elements commonly crystallize in the fcc structure:
Al, Ca, Ni, Cu, Sr, Rh, Pd, Ag, Ir, Pt, Au, Pb, Ce, Yb, Th
@item The following elements commonly crystallize in the hcp structure:
Be, Mg, Sc, Ti, Co, Zn, Y, Zr, Tc, Ru, Cd, Hf, Re, Os, Tl, Gd,
Tb, Dy, Ho, Er, Tm, Lu
@item The following elements commonly crystallize in the diamond structure:
C, Si, Ge, alpha-Sn
@item Included in this section are these examples of disordered pure elements:
Ga, In, S, white-Sn, As
@end table


